        </table>



        <p><strong>Fee winner: BonkBot</strong> ” Its flat 0.5% fee with no hidden costs is the most transparent and competitive for Solana-only traders. For multi-chain traders, Trojan's tiered structure (0.6% for high-volume) is the best value given its feature set.</p>



        <div class="pro-tip">

            <strong>�™� Fee Optimization Tip</strong>

            <p>Priority fees are where most traders overpay. All four bots default to aggressive priority fee bidding to ensure fast execution, but you can often reduce priority fees by 50-70% during low-traffic periods (weekends, Asian night hours) without sacrificing execution speed. Configure your bot to use adaptive priority fees, or manually set lower fees during off-peak hours.</p>

        </div>



        <!-- ============================================ -->

        <h2>4. Speed Benchmarks: Who Gets the Fill First?</h2>



        <p>In meme coin trading, milliseconds matter. We aggregated real-world benchmarks from Discord trading communities and independent speed tests conducted in Q1-Q2 2026. These are measured from "submit" to "confirmed transaction" for a standard swap on Solana with a 0.01 SOL priority fee:</p>



        <table>

            <thead>

                <tr>

