        <p><strong>Security winner: Tie ” Trojan, BonkBot, Banana Gun</strong> ” All three have clean security records. Maestro's 2024 DNS hijack incident was not a smart contract exploit but rather a front-end attack where users visiting Maestro's website had their approval requests redirected. Maestro compensated affected users and implemented additional security measures, but the incident does weigh on their track record.</p>



        <div class="warning-box">

            <strong>�� Telegram Bot Safety Golden Rules</strong>

            <p>1. <strong>Never use the same wallet for a trading bot that holds your long-term positions.</strong> Create a dedicated trading wallet with only the SOL you're willing to trade that day.</p>

            <p>2. <strong>Revoke token approvals regularly.</strong> Use Solscan or RugCheck to revoke approvals to any bot you're not actively using.</p>

            <p>3. <strong>Never click links from Telegram DMs claiming to be bot support.</strong> Real bot support will never message you first. Scammers impersonate bot admins constantly.</p>

            <p>4. <strong>Use a hardware wallet for storage, never for trading bots.</strong> Ledger and Trezor cannot sign the rapid transactions that Telegram bots require.</p>

            <p>5. <strong>Check the official bot username carefully.</strong> Scam bots use similar names (e.g., "TrojanBot" vs "Trojan_Bot") to trick users. Always verify the exact Telegram handle from the bot's official documentation.</p>

        </div>



        <!-- ============================================ -->

        <h2>8. Which Bot for Which Strategy?</h2>



        <p>The best bot depends entirely on <em>how</em> you trade. Here's our strategy-specific recommendations:</p>



        <h3>�� New Token Sniping</h3>

        <p><strong>Winner: Banana Gun</strong> ” Its raw speed advantage and aggressive anti-rug checks make it the best choice for buying tokens within seconds of launch. Set up a "buy preset" with your target slippage and priority fee, monitor new pool alerts in the bot, and execute with a single tap. Banana Gun's honeypot detection has saved users from countless rug pulls.</p>



        <h3>�œŠ Swing Trading Established Meme Coins</h3>

        <p><strong>Winner: Trojan</strong> ” Trojan's trailing take-profit feature, limit orders, and multi-chain support make it ideal for swing trading established tokens like DOGE, SHIB, PEPE, BONK, and WIF. Set a trailing TP at 30% and let the bot automatically sell when the price peaks and retraces ” even if you're asleep.</p>



        <h3>�œ� Copy Trading Alpha Wallets</h3>

        <p><strong>Winner: Maestro</strong> ” Maestro's copy trading module is the gold standard. Follow specific wallets, set copy multipliers (1x, 2x, 5x), configure max buy sizes per trade, and add a delay to avoid being front-run. Combine with wallet watchlists for a semi-automated alpha pipeline.</p>



        <h3>�˜ Casual / Beginner Trading</h3>

        <p><strong>Winner: BonkBot</strong> ” If you trade less than $5K per month and want a no-fuss experience, BonkBot is your bot. Low fees, zero configuration required, and smart defaults that keep you safe. You won't get the fastest fills, but you also won't accidentally set your slippage to 50% and get sandwiched.</p>



        <h3>�Œ‰ Multi-Chain Arbitrage</h3>

        <p><strong>Winner: Trojan (tie) / Maestro (tie)</strong> ” For traders who need to move between Solana, Ethereum, Base, and BNB Chain, both Trojan and Maestro offer robust multi-chain support. Trojan has better execution quality per chain; Maestro has more chains available. Pick based on your specific chain coverage needs.</p>



