        <h2>9. Setup Guides for Each Bot</h2>



        <p>Here's how to get each bot up and running in under 10 minutes:</p>



        <h3>�� BonkBot Setup</h3>

        <ol>

            <li>Open Telegram and search for <code>@bonkbot_bot</code> (verify the blue checkmark).</li>

            <li>Click <strong>Start</strong> ” the bot will show a welcome message with your unique deposit address.</li>

            <li>Send SOL to the deposit address. No minimum deposit, but 0.1 SOL is recommended for gas + a few trades.</li>

            <li>Type <code>/start</code> to see the main menu. Use <code>/buy [token_address] [SOL_amount]</code> to place your first trade.</li>

            <li>Configure slippage with <code>/settings</code> ” the default "Auto" works well for most trades.</li>

        </ol>



        <h3>�Œ Banana Gun Setup</h3>

        <ol>

            <li>Open Telegram and search for <code>@BananaGun_bot</code> (verify the blue checkmark).</li>

            <li>Click <strong>Start</strong> and type <code>/new_wallet</code> to generate a wallet, or <code>/import_wallet</code> to import an existing private key.</li>

            <li>Fund the wallet with SOL.</li>

            <li>Type <code>/start</code> and then use <code>s [token_address] [SOL_amount]</code> for instant buy, or <code>/snip [token_address] [SOL_amount]</code> for snipe mode.</li>

            <li>Configure anti-rug settings with <code>/settings</code> ” enable honeypot check, max tax check, and liquidity lock verification.</li>

        </ol>



        <h3>��œ Trojan Setup</h3>

        <ol>

            <li>Open Telegram and search for <code>@TrojanTradingBot</code> (verify the blue checkmark).</li>

            <li>Click <strong>Start</strong> and type <code>/new</code> to create a new wallet or <code>/import</code> to import one.</li>

            <li>Send SOL to the generated deposit address.</li>

            <li>Type <code>/settings</code> to configure: set default slippage (8-15% for meme coins), priority fee (0.005-0.01 SOL for normal traffic, 0.03-0.05 SOL for launches), and enable anti-sandwich mode.</li>

            <li>Use <code>/buy [token_address] [SOL_amount]</code> for standard buys. For limit orders, use <code>/limit [token_address] [target_price] [amount]</code>.</li>

            <li>Set a trailing take-profit: <code>/tp [token_address] [trail_percentage]</code> (e.g., <code>/tp PEPE 30</code> for a 30% trailing TP).</li>

        </ol>



        <h3>�Ž� Maestro Setup</h3>

        <ol>

            <li>Open Telegram and search for <code>@MaestroBOT</code> (verify the blue checkmark).</li>

            <li>Click <strong>Start</strong> and type <code>/createwallet</code> or <code>/importwallet</code>.</li>

            <li>Fund the wallet with the native token of the chain you're trading (SOL for Solana, ETH for Ethereum, etc.).</li>

            <li>For basic trading: <code>/buy [token_address] [amount]</code>. For sniping: <code>/snipe [token_address] [amount]</code>.</li>

            <li>For copy trading: <code>/copy add [wallet_address]</code> to start copying a wallet. Configure copy parameters with <code>/copysettings</code>.</li>

            <li>Set limit orders with <code>/limitbuy [token_address] [target_price] [amount]</code>.</li>

        </ol>



        <div class="highlight-box">

            <strong>�œ‹ Universal Setup Checklist (Do This for Every Bot)</strong>

            <p>� Create a dedicated hot wallet (never your main wallet)<br>

            � Fund with only what you're willing to lose in a single session<br>

            � Set slippage to 8-15% (never default to unlimited)<br>

            � Enable private mempool or Jito bundle routing<br>

            � Disable auto-approve for unknown tokens<br>

            � Set a max buy/sell limit per transaction<br>

            � Save the bot's official Telegram handle (protect against phishing)<br>

            � Write down your wallet seed phrase offline</p>

        </div>



        <!-- ============================================ -->

        <h2>10. The Verdict: Which Bot Wins in 2026?</h2>



        <div class="verdict-box">

            <h3>�† Overall Winner: Trojan</h3>

            <p><strong>Trojan wins our 2026 comparison</strong> because it offers the best balance of speed, features, fees, security, and multi-chain support. It's not the absolute fastest (Banana Gun wins that category), the cheapest (BonkBot wins that), or the most feature-packed (Maestro wins that), but it's the most well-rounded bot that works for the widest range of traders and strategies.</p>

            <p>Trojan's trailing take-profit feature alone justifies the choice for swing traders, and its MEV protection suite + refund program give it a security edge that no other bot matches.</p>

        </div>



        <p><strong>But here's the secret the best traders know: you don't have to choose one.</strong> Many serious meme coin traders in 2026 run two or three bots simultaneously ” Banana Gun for sniping new launches, Trojan for swing trading existing positions, and Maestro for copy trading alpha wallets. Each bot has a specific job in their stack, and they use the best tool for each task.</p>



        <p>If you're just starting out, <strong>start with BonkBot or Banana Gun</strong>. Learn the basics of Telegram bot trading with a simple, safe setup. As your volume grows and your strategies evolve, add Trojan for advanced features and Maestro for copy trading. Build your bot stack the same way you build your portfolio ” start simple, iterate, and scale.</p>



        <p><strong>Remember the golden rule of Telegram bot security: dedicated wallet, revoke approvals, verify handles, and never risk more than you can afford to lose.</strong> Bots are tools, not guarantees. A good bot with a bad strategy will still lose money. But a good bot with a disciplined strategy is the closest thing to an edge in the chaotic, beautiful world of meme coin trading.</p>



